<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870303-0084 </DOCNO><HL> Dividend News:Jacobson Stores Inc.Splits Stock 3-for-2,Slates Rise in Payout</HL><DD> 03/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> JCBSDIVIDENDS (DIV) </IN><DATELINE> JACKSON, Mich.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Jacobson Stores Inc. declared a 3-for-2 stock split, payable March 30 to stock of record March 13.    The specialty department stores company also announced a quarterly dividend of 11 cents a share after the split. It had been paying 12 1/2 cents a pre-split share. The action in effect raises the quarterly dividend 32%. The split would increase the number of shares outstanding to about 5.4 million from 3.6 million.    The new dividend is payable April 14 to stock of record March 30.    J.R. Fowler, chairman, said the increased payout is &quot;consistent with earnings and the favorable business outlook.&quot;    Jacobson Stores earned $4.2 million, or $1.10 a share, on sales of $203.5 million in the 39-week period ended Oct. 25. The company is expected to announce results for the fiscal year ended Jan. 31 next week. Company officials have said the fiscal year &quot;should be another record&quot; earnings year for the company.    Jacobson shares closed yesterday at $49.25, up 50 cents, in national over-the-counter trading. </TEXT></DOC>